Curious about my tools?

In case you were curious about the highly specific sort of workflow I’ve created, here’s a very skippable section where I’ll list what I use on a daily basis, and why I use it.

Digital Tools

Note-taking Software

  • [object HTMLImageElement]Obsidian
    • I really like Obsidian for its focus on local storage, meaning it works offline, and your work remains private. It’s also completely free and highly customizable, making it incredibly flexible. I use it for many personal and professional tasks, and the fact that it’s all in Markdown makes it easy to then export my work. This website is built out of those very same Markdown files!
